The paper deals with the problem of coordinating autonomous vehicles in a mobility-on-demand system, which involves aspects of control, robotics, and system optimization. Therefore, cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.RO (Robotics) are the most likely categories. The paper also uses queueing theory to model the system, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Finally, the paper uses linear programming to find an optimal rebalancing algorithm, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory).
